RACE.FOOTNOTES: EVANGELINE ALLONS rated two wide behind rivals as a three pronged battled went on up top, swung out seven to eight wide for the drive, rolled up outside rivals under right handed asks leaving mid stretch, took over with about a sixteenth to go and went clear at the wire. IMNOTONETOCOMPLAIN rated off the pace while saving ground, eased out near mid stretch, worked between runners and kept on gamely while earning the place. IMAGINE VICTORY , off slowly after being a bit rank and hopping, lagged off the pace while saving ground, angled wide into the lane, worked well out in the course in deep stretch and rallied. FANCY PRINCESS , between foes and in range of the duel, was kept in entering the lane, bid between horses in mid stretch but flattened out late. TWELVEO'CLOCKROCK disputed the pace three deep, drifted out leaving the three sixteenths, was corrected with right handed asks then faded. LADY CINCO DE MAYO broke a step slow, rushed up five wide early, chased four wide outside rivals into the lane, had aim, failed to kick on in mid stretch and gave way. SASSY BABE sped clear in the initial strides, was hooked from both sides, dueled between rivals into and around the turn, stayed on to mid stretch then gave way. ELLIE VICTORINA was hustled up soon after the break and challenged to the inside of runners, battled inside a pair around the turn, kept on past the three sixteenths then weakened late. CREATIVE CADENCE was sent up along the rail soon after the break then was rated off the leading trio, tracked inside around the turn, failed to go on in upper stretch and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALVY , forwardly placed into the first turn, tracked inside and awaited room behind the leading trio leaving the far turn, responded when roused and split rivals entering the lane, took over to the inside of FOWL NATION in upper stretch, spurted clear under stout asks in mid stretch, kept on under firm handling and denied STEELE MONEY through the final sixteenth. STEELE MONEY stalked two to three wide behind the leaders, angled out and was pushed along leaving the three eighths, circled five wide with an advance into the lane, threatened the winner in upper stretch, kept on gamely but was held at bay. HE'S ON FIRE cleared near the seven eighths, dropped in and set the early pace, met outside bids near the five eighths, dueled to the three eighths, was urged along trying to keep pace past the five sixteenths then gave way grudgingly in the final furlong. BLOWN SAVE , off the pace, was under pressure around the final turn while removed from the rail, swung six wide for the drive but came up empty. FOWL NATION reared up when fractious in the paddock, broke alertly, bid between foes nearing the five eighths, dueled, shook clear after six furlongs, was engaged from both sides in upper stretch and weakened through the final sixteenth. IRISH WARLOCK , keyed up five wide soon into the backstretch, pulled his way forward four wide and took over leaving the five furlong pole, sparred into and around the far turn, failed to go on nearing the quarter pole, faltered and was eased late.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JACKIE A edged up between rivals early, stalked behind the leaders leaving the far turn, worked through a seam in upper stretch, closed in under pressure and engaged the WORKIN ON A DREAM in mid stretch, dueled, wrested command in deep stretch and held firm. WORKIN ON A DREAM vied outside a rival into the first turn, went clear into the backstretch and set the pace towards the rail, kept rivals at bay around the final turn, came off the inside with the advantage into the stretch, dug in when collared leaving the furlong grounds, battled gamely inside the winner, ceded command inside the sixteenth pole but stayed well to preserve the place. ONE TWO KID was taken four wide for the backstretch, moved up into the far turn, continued four wide with aim through the drive but failed to follow through. COLBALOAF had speed to the inside of WORKIN ON A DREAM, rated off that one and stalked through the backstretch, steadied in a bit tight leaving the three sixteenths, angled out and closed steadily. STRONG HEADED dropped in early and drafted off the pace, came off the inside leaving the far turn, angled five wide for the drive, straightened and finished with good energy to gain. SEMPER FI prompted the pace two wide, was urged along past the five sixteenths, guided three wide allowing a path to the winner entering the lane and faded. DIXIE DRAWL stalked three wide, was pushed along between runners past the five sixteenths and faded. KENDAMA broke outward and hit the gate, stumbled then recovered to save ground, checked sharply around the first turn, regrouped and raced inside, edged up a bit saving ground past mid stretch then flattened out. JOHNG was steadied when in close into the first turn, raced off the pace, traveled between runners past the five sixteenths but lacked a bid. SUMMER SILENCE failed to menace.
